wikipedia_page.main: Major Sir Richard Whieldon Barnett (6 December 1863 – 17 October 1930) was an Irish barrister, sportsman, volunteer officer and freemason who sat as a Member of Parliament in the United Kingdom House of Commons. He also competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics.

response: The St Pancras West by-election of 1916 was held on 16 October 1916.  The by-election was held due to the resignation of the incumbent Conservative MP, Felix Cassel to become Judge Advocate General of the Armed Forces.  It was won by the Conservative candidate Richard Barnett, who was unopposedPage 44, British Parliamentary Election Results 1885–1918, edited by F. W. S. Craig due to the War-time electoral pact.
